            "hazard_name": [
                "systemic_toxicity_single_exposure"
            ],
            "hazard_statement": [
                "Suspected of damaging fertility or the unborn child"
            ],
            "rationale": [
                "Based on the evidence of abnormal behaviour of the offspring such as delayed response in head turning in a geotaxis test and delayed bar-holding response following intraperitoneal injection of the substance (140ng Be/mouse per day), described in EHC 106 (1990) (though no data are available on maternal toxicity). As for the reproductive toxicity of beryllium compounds, refer to \"ID485, Beryllium Oxide, CAS: 1304-56-9.\"\n"
